The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Soni gets Bengal

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 New Delhi, Nov. 23: Sonia Gandhi in a minor rejig of the party organisation gave Ambika Soni additional charge of Bengal, Tamil Nadu, Pondicherry and Andaman and Nicobar Islands.

 Soni, an AICC general secretary, is currently in charge of Jammu and Kashmir and Himachal Pradesh, besides the Congress presidents office, the party?s working committee and its central election committee.

 The states allocated to her were in the care of Salman Khursheed before he was appointed Uttar Pradesh Congress chief. An AICC release said the reallocation is temporary.

 Former Kerala chief minister and CWC member A.K. Antony has been put in charge of Karnataka, which was earlier with Vilasrao Deshmukh, who recently became the chief minister of Maharashtra.

 The media had earlier speculated that Soni and Antony were likely inductions in the Manmohan Singh cabinet during an expansion.

 General secretary Margaret Alva has been given additional charge of Chhattisgarh.




